    &lt;configuration&gt;
       &lt;minimizeJar&gt;true&lt;/minimizeJar&gt;
       &lt;filters&gt;
           &lt;filter&gt;
               &lt;artifact&gt;org.postgresql:postgresql&lt;/artifact&gt;
               &lt;includes&gt;
                   &lt;include&gt;**&lt;/include&gt;
               &lt;/includes&gt;
           &lt;/filter&gt;
       &lt;/filters&gt;
   &lt;/configuration&gt;

For more details: [Selecting Contents for Uber JAR][1].

The issue occurs due to the (unfiltered) `&lt;minimizeJar&gt;true&lt;/minimizeJar&gt;` configuration in your POM, and the fact that the driver class is not used at compile time.

maven-shade-plugin on [`minimizeJar`][2]:
&gt; When true, dependencies will be stripped down on the class level to only the transitive hull required for the artifact.

  [1]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-shade-plugin/examples/includes-excludes.html
  [2]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-shade-plugin/shade-mojo.html#minimizeJar

